  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Missing Polish Translations on /pl/about/ Page\n\nThe Polish version of the about page (/pl/about/) contains untranslated content that should be localized to Polish.\n\nRequirements:\n- Audit the /pl/about/ page to identify all untranslated text\n- Translate missing content from English (or source language) to Polish\n- Ensure translations maintain the original meaning and tone\n- Verify all UI elements, headings, body text, and buttons are translated\n- Check for hardcoded English strings in the template or component code\n- Validate that date formats, number formats, and other locale-specific formatting follow Polish conventions\n- Test the page to ensure layout works properly with Polish text lengths\n- Confirm no encoding issues with Polish special characters (ą, ć, ę, ł, ń, ó, ś, ź, ż)\n\nEdge cases to consider:\n- Dynamic content that may bypass translation system\n- Pluralization rules specific to Polish language\n- Content pulled from external sources or APIs\n- Alt text for images and accessibility labels",
